      "content": "No, an AI cannot currently take over your entire online life or impersonate you in real-time without your consent. While generative AI can easily create convincing text that mimics your style based on your past social media data, the rumors you're seeing are likely either automated bots using third-party \"clone AI\" marketing accounts, deepfakes for satire, or sophisticated phishing scams rather than a literal AI takeover. If you truly want to protect your digital identity, you should strictly review your privacy settings and consider disabling the \"email from outside your network\" or \"sponsored\" features on your social accounts to prevent impersonation.",
